#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Despite everything, 2020 was a great year for Tails. We released major "
"improvements that made Tails easier to use by the people who need it the "
"most."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you enjoyed our work in 2020, take a minute now to\n"
"<a href=\"https://tails.boum.org/donate/?r=at\">donate and fight surveillance and censorship</a>!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"From the number of automatic upgrades, we know that Tails was used 20% more "
"in 2020 than in 2019, which is our largest increase since 2016. From March "
"to May only, when the lockdown measures were the strictest worldwide, Tails "
"got used 10% more than ever before."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Today, Tails is used close to 32&#8239;000 times each day."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!img users.png link=\"no\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Simplified starting procedure"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We added support for **Secure Boot** in April. Secure Boot doesn't really "
"make your computer any safer but it forced most users to edit their BIOS in "
"complicated and risky ways to be able to use Tails (or Linux in general).  "
"Now you don't have to edit the BIOS anymore!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We also documented the **Shift+Restart** procedure to start Tails from "
"Windows 8 or 10 using the **Start [[!img lib/start.png alt=\"\" link=\"no"
"\"]]** menu.  Now you don't have to hammer that Boot Menu key anymore!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"All this dramatically simplified our [[starting instructions for PCs|install/"
"windows#restart]]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!img install/inc/screenshots/choose_an_option.png link=\"no\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Better upgrades"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Because we know that upgrades are one of the most painful aspects of using "
"Tails, we released significant improvements to automatic upgrades in "
"January.  We made automatic upgrades:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"Available **from all prior versions** to the latest version in a single "
"upgrade."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  For example, you can upgrade from 4.10 to 4.14 directly, without\n"
"  having to first upgrade to 4.12 anymore.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Available **endlessly between minor versions** of Tails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  For example, you don't have to do a manual upgrade anymore after a few\n"
"  upgrades. You will only have to do a manual upgrade between major versions,\n"
"  for example to upgrade to Tails 5.0 at the end of 2021.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Use less memory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Better documented, especially manual upgrades."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "But also&hellip;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We completely redesigned our Home page to explain better what is Tails and "
"why people should use it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "  [[!img about/footprints.svg link=\"no\" alt=\"\" size=\"300x\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We made it possible to save the settings of the Welcome Screen in the "
"Persistent Storage: language, keyboard, and additional settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "  [[!img news/version_4.8/welcome_screen.png link=\"no\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We simplified the verification procedure on our download page by [[replacing "
"the *Tails Verification* extension|verification_extension_deprecation]] with "
"similar JavaScript code that runs directly on the page."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  People without JavaScript are also now pointed to the checksum of the\n"
"  download.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "  [[!img verify.png link=\"no\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We added support for the **hardware cryptocurrency wallets** Trezor and "
"Ledger."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Under the hood"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, the biggest part of our work doesn't lead to such major "
"changes for our users. Tails is an endless work of updates and maintenance: "
"publishing a new release every 4 weeks to fix security vulnerabilities, "
"adapting to new versions of the underlying software, keeping our website and "
"development infrastructure secure and reliable, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We published **more releases than ever**. In 2020 we released 15 new "
"versions of Tails to always have your back covered!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  At the end of 2019, Firefox switched from releasing a new version every 6\n"
"  weeks to releasing a new version every 4 weeks. And so did we.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"We streamlined our release process by automating its most time-consuming "
"parts. This reduced the work needed to publish a new release of Tails from 2 "
"full days of work to only 1 day."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  In the long run, this will help us spend more time on what really\n"
"  matters to our users and allow us to react faster to emergencies\n"
"  in case of security vulnerabilities.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- We migrated to GitLab and saw many more of you jump in and give us a hand!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Help us fight surveillance and censorship"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "[[!img donate/godzilla.png link=\"no\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"All our work is made possible by donations from people like you. We "
"particularly appreciate monthly and yearly donations, even the smallest "
"ones.  Because they help us plan our work, they are the most valuable for "
"the sustainability of Tails."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you enjoyed our work in 2020, take a minute now to donate and fight "
"surveillance and censorship!"
msgstr ""

